BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: set theList to paragraphs of text of (do shell script "pmset -g batt")set percent to word 6 of theList's item 2set charge to word 7 of theList's item 2if (charge = "charging" or charge = "finishing") then	set iconC to "â¬†"else if (charge = "AC") then	set iconC to "â¥‘"else if (charge = "charged") then	return "ðŸ”‹"else	set iconC to ""end ifset remainingRaw to my split(theList's item 2, " ")set remainingTime to remainingRaw's item 5if (remainingTime = "(no") then	set strTime to " (?)"else if (remainingTime = "0:00") then	set strTime to ""else	set strTime to " (" & remainingTime & ")"end ifreturn iconC & percent & "%"to split(someText, delimiter)	set AppleScript's text item delimiters to delimiter	set someText to someText's text items	set AppleScript's text item delimiters to {""}	return someTextend split

BTTTriggers.BTTInlineAppleScript: if application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		if player state is playing then			next track		end if	end tellend ifif application "Spotify" is running then	tell application "Spotify"		if player state is playing then			next track		end if	end tellend if

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: if application "Spotify" is running then	tell application "Spotify"		if player state is playing then			return (get artist of current track) & " - " & (get name of current track)		else			return ""		end if	end tellend ifif application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		if player state is playing then			return (get artist of current track) & " - " & (get name of current track)		else			return ""		end if	end tellend ifreturn ""

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: # This script requires two libs. Download them:# https://itunes.apple.com/ru/app/json-helper-for-applescript/id453114608?l=en&mt=12 # https://itunes.apple.com/ru/app/location-helper-for-applescript/id488536386?mt=12# Modify settings below to suit your preferencesset units to "imperial" #metric, imperialset tempDisplay to "Â°F" #Â°C,Â°Fset appid to "32c4256d09a4c52b38aecddba7a078f6" #App ID for OpenWeatherMaptell application "Location Helper"	set clocation_coords to [40.73061, -73.935242]	tell application "JSON Helper"		set weather to fetch JSON from "http://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?lat=" & item 1 of clocation_coords & "&lon=" & item 2 of clocation_coords & "&units=" & units & "&appid=" & appid		set temp to temp of main of weather as string		set cond_icon to icon of item 1 of weather of weather as string		if cond_icon is in ["01d", "01n"] then			set cond to "â˜€ï¸"		else if cond_icon is in ["02d", "02n"] then			set cond to "â›…ï¸"		else if cond_icon is in ["03d", "03n", "04d", "04n"] then			set cond to "â˜ï¸"		else if cond_icon is in ["09d", "09n"] then			set cond to "ðŸŒ§"		else if cond_icon is in ["10d", "10n"] then			set cond to "ðŸŒ¦"		else if cond_icon is in ["11d", "11n"] then			set cond to "ðŸŒ©"		else if cond_icon is in ["13d", "13n"] then			set cond to "â„ï¸"		else if cond_icon is in ["50d", "50n"] then			set cond to "ðŸŒ«"		else			set cond to ""		end if		set temp_round to round (temp * 1.0)		return cond & " " & temp_round & tempDisplay	end tellend tell

BTTTriggers.BTTInlineAppleScript: set curVolume to get volume settingsif output muted of curVolume is false then	set volume with output mutedelse	set volume without output mutedend iftry	output muted of (get volume settings)end try

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: set curVolume to get volume settingsoutput muted of curVolume

BTTTriggers.BTTInlineAppleScript: if application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes" to playpauseelse	tell application "Spotify" to playpauseend if

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: if application "Spotify" is running then	tell application "Spotify"		if player state is playing then return "pause"	end tellend ifif application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		if player state is playing then return "pause"	end tellend ifreturn "play"
